<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4DB0FF68FDFC5D10" blockId="24.[145,761,197,526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4DB0FF68FD045FC7" box="[145,761,197,219]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Additions to Stephenson’s original description:</emphasis>
Chaetae ~75 µm long. Epidermis covered with rows of pale gland cells and deeply staining granular gland cells. Dorsal vessel with peristomial bifurcation. Nephridia (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4C94FEEDFDE75E48" box="[437,538,320,342]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="21.[827,909,748,770]" captionTargetBox="[830,1438,198,705]" captionTargetId="figure-716@21.[827,1441,195,708]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 12. Marionina grisea. A, BMNH 1933.2.23.902, spermatheca. B, BMNH 1933.2.23.901, segments VIII–X. C, BMNH 1933.2.23.902, male apparatus. Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461119/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
) in 7/8–10/11 and postclitellar segments. Ventral nerve cord with small anterior subbuccal bulb; see 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4CD0FED3FD8C5E8E" authorityName="Michaelsen" authorityYear="1890" box="[497,625,382,403]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4CD0FED3FD8C5E8E" box="[497,625,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Marionina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
discussion above. Sperm funnels ≥ 450 µm long, 160 µm wide. Spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="130F6EE4FFA8FFCC4C69FE17FE555ECD" box="[328,424,442,464]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="21.[827,909,748,770]" captionTargetBox="[830,1438,198,705]" captionTargetId="figure-716@21.[827,1441,195,708]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 12. Marionina grisea. A, BMNH 1933.2.23.902, spermatheca. B, BMNH 1933.2.23.901, segments VIII–X. C, BMNH 1933.2.23.902, male apparatus. Abbreviations are defined under ‘Taxonomy’. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461119/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
) ≥ 300 µm long, 110 µm wide at duct and 70 µm wide at ampulla, with glands ~75 µm wide surrounding pore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B7261FFA8FFCC4DB0FD9BFE485D76" blockId="24.[145,760,566,619]" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4DB0FD9BFEFE5D56" box="[145,259,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is discussed together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4DB0FDFBFEEB5D76" authorityName="Stephenson" authorityYear="1932" box="[145,278,598,619]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aestuum">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4DB0FDFBFEEB5D76" box="[145,278,598,619]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M. aestuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3409E2FFA8FFCC4C6FFDFBFE505D77" box="[334,429,597,619]" class="Clitellata" family="Enchytraeidae" genus="Marionina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enchytraeida" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis id="B940AE73FFA8FFCC4C6FFDFBFE505D77" box="[334,429,597,619]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="1127">M. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
